Reasoning: The paper deals with the sensitivity and block sensitivity of Boolean functions, which are topics in computational complexity theory and discrete mathematics. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves information theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category. Additionally, the concept of block sensitivity is related to computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible sub-category as well.
